1. open anaconda prompt

2.To change your diretory using command 
>D:\cd D:\vs_code_workspace
type code to open vs code
>code . 

3. To create environment in vs code
>conda create -p venv python==3.9 -y

3.1. To clear screen
>cls

4.To activate conda environment
>conda activate venv/

5.To install packages in text file

>pip install -r filename.txt

6.to create jupyter notebook in vs code
Make a newfile filename.ipynb
>pip install ipykernel

